review_blob:
Dubina Bell Road IPA

Poured from 16oz Dubina growler 
Color: very nice golden golden color with small to medium head 
Aroma: big whiff of grapefruit/tropical fruits with a little pine
Flavor: it is very balance. You got your pine/hop resin along with a great juicy/tropical character.

Overall: easily top 5 IPA in Arizona and hope it makes its way to cans some day

San tan kilohop

Copper color little head.

Heavy citrus hop aroma, getting some lemon. Smells fantastic 

Malty, honey and little sweet. Good but taste doesn't live up to small.

On draft at Dragoon, 6oz pour

Dark Mahogany color, not much head.

Smells rich and sweet, maybe caramel?, almost like an old ale.

Sweet malty taste; toffee, caramel.. Finished with whiskey finishes with finishes with touch of alcohol.

The sweetness of the beer blends beautifully with the flavor of barrel.

This is top 2 barleywines I've ever had, neck and neck with smog city bourbon OE and possibly best beer ever brewed in Arizona.

Appearance- one of the most beautiful beers you will ever look at... Violet deep ruby

Aroma- Im not that familiar with dragonfruit but Ive been told this is good representation of the smell with a subtle pickle-ey smell.

Taste- your mouth Immediately gets a berry / fruity flavor followed by lacto sourness

Overall- my first official Florida-weisse and Its perfect and I hope its not the last. I wont be surprised if this is the best one because I hear Wakefield is the king of Berliners
beer_name: J. Wakefield Dragonfruit Passion Fruit (DFPF) Berliner Weisse

review_blob:
Bright golden color nice thick white head. Nose gets sucker punched by the aroma of the Nelson and Mosaic - Earthy, tropical fruit. 

Nice tropical citrus flavor, finishes dry and bitter. 
This beer could have brewed on the west coast and fit right in. Just a well rounded ipa. Definitely cant tell its 7.90%

Honey wine fermented with a blend of Honey wine fermented with a blend of Marion berries, raspberries, and blueberries. This is a sparkling version of the Marion berry. The bubbliness makes all the flavors just pop. Deep dark purple color. Sweet berry flavor. Perfect mead
Honey wine fermented with a blend of Marion berries, raspberries, and blueberries. Deep dark purple color. Sweet berry flavor. This is fantastic
Pours a nice golden color. Nice sweet nose. Pleasant maple flavor without being over the top.
Not their best effort. Dry mead aged in Hungarian oak. Too boozy and hot for my taste
A sour mead? Yes please! Nice amber color. Sweet than tart. Unusual combination but works well
Dark burgundy pour with aromas of berries and vanilla. The flavors of berries and Vanilla merry together beautifully. Hard to believe this isn't my favorite of the dayl
Bottle shared by daknole. Aroma of wine grapes, honey, and oak. Deep purple color. Similar to cabernet version just not as complex but getting a hint of chocolate. Another winner By superstition
Bottle shared by daknole. Aroma of wine grapes, honey, and oak. Deep purple color. Similar to cabernet version just not as complex. Least favorite of aphrodisia series.. Still excellent though
Bottle shared by daknole. Aroma of wine grapes, honey, and oak. Deep purple color. Similar to cabernet version just not as complex. Still excellent though
Deep purple color. Heavy cab flavor followed by sweetness of mead. Great tannin. Fantastic blend
Pours an absolutely stunning clear golden color. Aroma and taste of fresh lemon, like a lemonhead. Citra hop finish. 4 pounds of lemon zest used. Adam nailed this one!

Pours blackest of black with little head. Nose is nice and smokey but not over powering, with a hint of jalapenos. Flavor is perfect blend of smokey, spicy, and chocolate. Wilderness continues to impress.
Holy balls, best variant of hunahpu variant ever. Incrdidbly complex flavors. The port barrels plays so nice with the chocolate chili flavors of the base beer. Perfect chili stout.
beer_name: Cigar City Hunahpus Imperial Stout - Double Barrel Aged

review_blob: Aroma: smells of sweet bourbon nectar. Nice amber hue with little head. Nice bourbon flavor up front followed by the sweet barleywine flavors. Great Beer from the boards.
beer_name: Arizona Wilderness Barely Wine Barley Wine - Pappy Van Winkle Barrel

review_blob: Hazy orange/yellow color. Smells of Orange, wheat, subtle salt. Tastes tart with Orange peel, wheat, coriander with hint of salt. Mimosa beer. Yums
Pours very dark brown out of tap at ratebeer sneek peak party. Aroma vanilla and brown sugar. Taste of roasted vanilla and subtle pecan. Very tasty!!
beer_name: Arizona Wilderness Picacho Pecan Pie Brown Ale

review_blob: Whoa, birthday beer courtesy of daknole. Fantastic floral nose. Great fruity brett character. Gorgeous beer
beer_name: Crooked Stave Wild Wild Brett Violet (WWBV)

review_blob: 22oz bottle purchased from a friend who bought at Belmont Station. I have to admit it.. I am a huge sucker for good berliners... and boy does this deliver. Nice funky sour smell.. In the taste the fruit flavors of hibiscus and pomegranate blend beautifully with the funkiness and sour flavors. I absolutely adore this beer - especially for the price.

pours a nice golden color with lots a bubbles.. think a cross between chardonnay and champagne. Im getting a lot of buttered popcorn like in a big buttery chardonnay.. Real tasty but I think age will do this beer good. WIll be aging my 2nd bottle for a bit.

Reddish pour out of Bottle as a gift for the wife from fellow Rateberr-er Daknole.. Aroma of berries, tart grapes, red wine vinegar, lactic sourness. Fruity and sour flavors. Pleasantly tart and acidic with a nice raspberry flavor. Avery really knocked this out the park, one of my favorite sours.

Bottle 84 of 300. Shared with my beer buddy daknole, yes that daknole :-). If there was a perfect barrel aged stout it would be this. Unbelievably complex. Coffee, vanilla, maple, oh my. Top 2 or 3 stouts all time.
Pours hazy yellow into glass. Clearly unfiltered and loving it. Nice hop nose - citrusy grapefruit tangerine and lemon. Taste citrus and resiness but very balanced and easy to drink. Lovely beer
Pours dark black out of bottle. Smells of freshly brewed coffee. Nice espresso, chocolate flavors. Nice variation of regular RIS.

This rating is for XII. poured of bottle found in tiny liquor store in San Diego. Pours blackest of black. Smells of licorice and sweet raisins. Heavy chocolate on initial sip ans finishes like a vania caramel latte. Incredibly smooth for 11.2%
Smells sweet with a little funk. Taste fruit with some strong Brett characteristics. Another strong beer by anchorage.
beer_name: Anchorage The Tide and Its Takers Triple

review_blob: On tap at Ground Control. Poured into 8oz snifter. Dark brown to black in color. Coffee and chocolate really come out in the aroma. Chocolate overpowers the coffee at a chilled temperature while the coffee pops through as it warms up. Super smooth for 9.2%. Very reminiscent, if not better than, Speedway Stout I had earlier that day.

Pours Dark Black into North Coast snifter and shared with Daknole. De Molens continues to impress with this stellar imperial stout. Pleasantly sweet and boozy. Hints of chocolate, vanilla, bourbon, oh my. Love it!
beer_name: De Molen Hel & Verdoemenis Wild Turkey BA

review_blob: Share with Daknole. Sweetness of plums overpowers the barnyard funk found in most gueuzes. Pleasantly sweet and subtle sourness. Very refreshing.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Poured into north coast brewing snifter and shared with my wife stephanie and ratebeer legend daknole. An American wild ale that could pass for true Belgian gueuze - it has the Belgian Barnyard nose usually lacking in most American sours. Nice refreshing sour flavor that lingers well.  An absolute treat to drink.
